<br>
Guilds agree to a 12 hour waiting period on a ragefire pop, if there is a camp currently being held, before the camp goes to FFA. <br>
<br>
While I personally would <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> not</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> take a ragefire even after a 12 hour period had I known there was a cleric camping there for weeks, it would serve to allow people from all sized guilds a fair and equal chance to get their cleric's epics (likely the *first and only* cleric epic for a guild of that size). Any guild/group of people that could not raise a force capable of killing ragefire in 12 hours, probably would not have even been able to raise the people needed for the King part of the epic anyway, ensuring that the time period is only used to hold people at bay for a reasonable time before going FFA on this highly valuable mob. <br>
<br>
In this instance, the fact that CoN's cleric was AFK would not have mattered at pop time: A cleric would have 12 hours to amass a force capable of taking the dragon easily within 12 hours, due primarily to the shows of support from Noble Blade and others in this regard. <br>
<br>
It would also prevent people from &quot;ganking&quot; the camp out from under people. I would honestly shudder to think what a FFA ragefire would look like in Skyfire, if that is what it came down to. <br>
<br>
Ignoring the list is fine, since it is not offical. Ignoring a cleric who had been camped in the zone, trying to organize and engage the dragon, is not fine, and leads to a FFA ragefire camp, which is something that no one, hopefully, wants to see. <br>
<br>
Yers,<br>
<br>
